# @homeos/web — environment template (Vite)
# Copy to a local env file, then edit:   cp env.example .env.local
# Vite loads .env.local (and .env) automatically; both are gitignored. NEVER commit real secrets.
#
# #225 — the web board now logs in with real Google auth via Supabase (PKCE + cookie session). The old
# build-embedded VITE_HOMEOS_READ_TOKEN / WRITE_TOKEN / MESSAGES_TOKEN are RETIRED: API calls now send the
# same-origin Supabase auth cookie (credentials:'include'), not a Bearer header. The two vars below are
# read by Vite at DEV and BUILD time. The PUBLISHABLE key is safe to ship in the public bundle; the
# service_role key is SERVER-ONLY and must NEVER appear here.

# ── Local run modes ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# UI-only (layout / theme / RTL): just `pnpm --filter @homeos/web dev` → http://localhost:5173.
#   The login screen renders; data-backed views show their loading/empty states without a backend.
#
# Real data + login: the dev server has NO proxy and the API server has NO CORS, so a split (5173 → 3000)
#   is blocked by the browser. Use SAME-ORIGIN instead:
#     1. set the two VITE_SUPABASE_* vars below (from your Supabase project)
#     2. pnpm --filter @homeos/web build      # bakes them into apps/web/dist
#     3. pnpm --filter @homeos/server dev      # serves that dist same-origin at :3000
#     4. open http://localhost:3000  (NOT :5173)
#   Leave VITE_HOMEOS_API_BASE unset for same-origin (so the auth cookie is sent automatically).
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Base URL of the @homeos/server API. UNSET / empty = same origin (the server serves apps/web/dist).
# Set ONLY for a split deploy where the API lives on a different origin (then the server needs CORS).
# VITE_HOMEOS_API_BASE=

# Supabase project URL (dashboard → Project Settings), e.g. https://<ref>.supabase.co. MUST match the
# server's SUPABASE_URL. Used to create the @supabase/ssr browser client (Google login + cookie session).
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=

# Supabase PUBLISHABLE key (dashboard → Project Settings → API), format sb_publishable_… . Safe to ship
# in the public bundle (it only permits anon/auth operations). NEVER put the service_role key here.
VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=
